# a [[storm]], [[tempest]]:
## a [[windstorm]]
##* '''905''', ''{{w|Kokin Wakashū}}'' (book 5, poem 249; also ''{{w|Ogura Hyakunin Isshu|Hyakunin Isshu}}'', poem 22)
##*: {{ja-usex|[[吹く]]からに[[秋]]の[[草%木]]の[[萎れる|しをる]]れば[[むべ]][[山風]]を'''嵐'''と[[言う|いふ]]らむ|ふく から に あき の くさ%き の しをるれば むべ やま-かぜ を '''あらし''' と いふらむ|rom=fuku kara ni aki no kusaki no shiorureba mube yama-kaze o '''arashi''' to iuran|The plants of autumn droop and wither at its touch―that explains, of course, why a '''wind''' from the mountains has come to be called a '''storm'''.<ref>{{cite-book|1985|Helen Craig McCullough |Kokin Wakashū: The First Imperial Anthology of Japanese Poetry : with {{w|Tosa Nikki}} and Shinsen Waka|edition=illustrated, reprint|publisher=Stanford University Press|isbn=0-8047-1258-1|page=63}}</ref>|sort=あらし}}
